				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Banned . . . for how long, forever?<a name="69748"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 15 04 1:43 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Funny thing.. people talk about how the EULA prohibits macros and sequences on gamepads, etc...
<br />

<br />
But I've read over the EULA several times recently, and could find no mention of such things.  No mention of any sort of &quot;unattended operation&quot; that people talk about.  All it talks about is using 3rd party software that affects gameplay.  This is so vague that GMs can choose to interpret it however they like, I believe.
<br />

<br />
I think most of &quot;what's prohibited by the EULA&quot; has become hearsay, and people just spread it from person to person, not actually double-checking that it's there somewhere.
<br />

<br />
If I'm wrong and someone can cite the exact paragraph where it talks about this, I'll eat my tattered leather cap 
