				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Banned . . . for how long, forever?<a name="69790"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 16 04 12:41 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The game is as SoE wants it to be.  Othelia is correct in saying that only the GM's will have the right to interpret the EULA.  
<br />

<br />
That being said,  I totally disagree with Othelia's rigid evaluation of the rule.  But that is Othelia's and SoE's purview.  Maybe time for me and my family guild to move on . . . no one will miss us.  And neither will SoE . . . 
<br />

<br />
I still don't get it.  A Nostromo pressing the &quot;1&quot; key every 11 seconds is not conspicuiously aggregious . . . Don't you think singing your Brass song in EC is just as bad as pressing the 1 key every 30 seconds?  Auto-circle to learn swimming, anyone?  I know playing a ranger, I use(d) one to Kick or Archery . .  and now they are gonna add auto-archery supposedly . . . before a rule break.  Now it's part of the game . . .
<br />

<br />
Anyway. . . . here is an account of the correspondence with the GM's. . . .
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">
<br />
To: EQAccountStatus; **GM**
<br />
Subject: FW: EverQuest Account Suspension
<br />

<br />
Would it be possible to understand how long my account has been suspended for? 
<br />

<br />
Also, I really would like to better understand where and when (if ever) a hardware device that repeats a single key stroke is acceptable to use with this game.
<br />

<br />
I personally did not interpret the Nostromo Game Pad I have pressing the same key over and over again while I sat here a violation of the EULA.
<br />

<br />
I am not certain how *modify game play* is interpreted.
<br />

<br />
To me this game is about completing levels in the lost dungeons of Norrath, helping friends to get their epics, breaking into the Plane of Fear. It is about teamwork and cooperation. It is, in short, a social game.
<br />

<br />
There have been many improvements to the UI and controls over time, rather than concessions or cheats, these are game improvements: sanctioned and introduced by Sony/Verant. (The spell book not taking the whole screen, the /book command, the /pause command, etc)
<br />

<br />
Hitting [Bash] then [Taunt] every five seconds until your fingers bleed is not a game; coordinating a raid against the mechanical behemoth is.
<br />

<br />
I can clearly see how third party tools (that I have heard about) like MacroQuest are clearly in violation of the EULA, but I really never believed that my Nostromo was.
<br />

<br />
Again, I was sitting here reading a book, practicing spells and waiting for the GM to respond to my name change petition. While I fully admit that I was not pressing the *1* key on my own every 11 seconds, I certainly could have been.
<br />

<br />
Is this really the kind of offense that you feel people should be suspended or banned for? In EQ2 you have fixed the *skills* process so that a character that levels up already gains the new skills that they achieve. In EQ1 this is much more problematic and it is really a necessity for a character that has leveled up quickly to practice spells over and over (in order to gain the skills required to cast without fizzling). Without these skill points they are of little use in a group.
<br />

<br />
If you tell me that I must press the *1* key over a thousand times on my own in order to level up my skills, and that this is indeed part of what you call the *game play* of the game; then I am sorry, for this is a poor sort of game in my opinion and I doubt that I will level up a new character ever again. 
<br />

<br />
Again, thank you for looking into this matter. I have always been a bit curious about the Nostromo. Everyone that I know (that still plays EQ - I myself have played from 2000 on) uses a Nostromo. Every warrior uses it for an auto [kick] [taunt], every paladin for [bash] [taunt] and every ranger for [Range Attack].
<br />

<br />
If these are all indeed violations, a more explicit warning in the EULA that better defined *modify game play* would be very much appreciated I would gather by both myself and the community at large.
<br />

<br />
Sincerely, 
<br />

<br />
**PLAYER** **PLAYER**
