<br />

<br />
Thank you for getting back to me. I appreciate your comments and your concerns on this situation. Modification of the gaming experience, whether it be through third party software(such as MacroQuest) or third party hardware(such as programming a programmable game pad) is not allowed. Macroing is accomplished in either of these scenarios, where players may achieve gain without effort, and where they in fact do not even have to be present. We also reserve the right to terminate game play if we feel that it is being done inappropriately.
<br />

<br />
The in game tells that I had sent you were to determine if you were, in fact, away from keyboard. I sent a tell to each character. Obviously if a character takes repetitive actions constantly, and they do not respond when contacted, then they are likely not present.
<br />

<br />
I understand your concerns when you say that hitting buttons repeatedly is &quot;not a game,&quot; and you are most welcome to have your opinions and feelings on the matter. However, the game has been designed in the way that it has. If you are unhappy with any content in the game, or with how anything is done, then we strongly encourage a /feedback with your ideas so it may reach our development team for consideration. Posting messages on our official message boards, located at U color=#0000ff www.everquestlive.com/U, is also an excellent way to get your concerns out. This way, the game may continue to change and evolve, as you have described with the UI and controls.
<br />

<br />
The suspensions will last for seven(7) days. Whether or not the accounts are banned is not my decision to make, so please contact EQAccountStatus@soe.sony.com for further information. 
<br />

<br />
I hope I have helped to answer your questions. Please feel free to respond.
<br />

<br />
**GM**
<br />
GM 
<br />
EverQuest Game Master
<br />

<br />
Sony Online Entertainment
<br />

<br />
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
<br />

<br />
My Reply:
<br />

<br />
Thank you for your prompt reply - and the advice.
<br />

<br />
I will be happy to post feedback using the in-game channels when they are once again available to me. If you think the message boards are an appropriate forum as well, I will be utilizing them.
<br />

<br />
To be blunt, I did not think gamepads were in violation of the EULA as it is written. I appreciate the clarification and will endeavor to encourage Sony via /feedback to be clearer in either the in-game Knowledge base or the web base.
<br />

<br />
Answer number 8349 was the only one I could find, and I interpreted this literally (macros are multiple step functions - not single repeated keys).
<br />

<br />
I have maintained three accounts (which I play simultaneously); have been a member since 2000 and even volunteered for the guide program for a while. That said it may be time to find a new game. I truly do not want to get carpel tunnel syndrome pressing 2, 3, 2, 3.
<br />

<br />
Many of my friends have left for other games. I have been loyal to this one, but if this truly is Sony's position (which I have no doubt in your succinct reply that it is). I may give away my gear and cancel my three accounts when all is said and done.
<br />

<br />
Knowing clearly what the rules are I will not break them. That is how I am. However, I believe I have lost my will to play.
<br />

<br />
Again, thank you for your prompt reply and your time.
<br />

<br />
--**PLAYER**
