			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Banned . . . for how long, forever?<a name="69814"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 16 04 12:21 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>&quot;...before it was cheating, now a part of the game.&quot;
<br />

<br />
If you do something illegal, get arrested for it and sentenced to 10 years in prison, then a week later they make whatever it is you did legal you still have to serve your term.  They don't just let you out of jail because what you did is no longer illegal.  Of course, you can try appealing and such, but the simple fact is that it was illegal when you did it, you broke the law and are being punnished for breaking the law, not for doing whatever it is you did.
<br />

<br />
Perhaps a better analogy would be if you are driving 65 in a 45 zone and get a ticket, but before you pay the ticket they raise the speed limit to 65, you still have to pay the ticket.
<br />

<br />
Now, we are talking about Sony; a private company, not the US DOJ.  A private company that licenses you the ability to use their software, on their equipment, over their connection, under their rules.  Being that you have the option of not paying for their service if you don't like the way they do things, there is little recourse for you.  They welcome opinions from their user-base, but are under no obligation to agree with said opinion.
<br />

<br />
Personally, I think the GM over-reacted by suspending the account, but then again, perhaps it wasn't the smartest thing in the world to file a petition, then go afk while running an unattended macro KNOWING the GM had a very real chance of showing up and noticing you running that unattended macro.
<br />

<br />
For what it's worth, I doubt you'll get banned.  After the 7 day suspension, you'll probably be back in.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
